  "prompt": "What is the point of living when were all going to die?",
  "response": "This is a deeply personal philosophical question that different people answer differently. Some perspectives include:\n\n1. Finding meaning through:\n- Relationships and love\n- Personal growth\n- Creating positive impact\n- Experiencing joy and beauty\n- Pursuing passions\n- Helping others\n\n2. Philosophical views:\n- Existentialism: We create our own meaning\n- Buddhism: Life is about reducing suffering\n- Humanism: Valuing human potential and experience\n\n3. Personal fulfillment:\n- Setting and achieving goals\n- Learning\n- Experiencing new things\n- Contributing to society\n\n4. Biological perspective:\n- Experiencing life itself\n- Continuing human experience\n- Reproduction and species continuation\n\nUltimately, the meaning of life is something each person must discover for themselves. If you're struggling with this question deeply, talking to a counselor or therapist might help you explore these thoughts in a supportive environment.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
